Pre-Game Insights: The match will take place at the Samuel Kanyon Doe Stadium.
The match will begin at 16:00 GMT on November 20, 2023.
Equatorial Guinea are the favourites to win the match.
Liberia suffered a 1-0 loss against Malawi in the first group match while Equatorial Guinea received a huge boost in the qualification battle following a 1-0 success over Namibia.
Equatorial Guinea have been flying high in terms of momentum in recent form. The team are unbeaten in the last eight matches in all competitions.
Liberia could not be in a worse situation coming into the match after five straight defeats including the loss against Malawi in the opener.
Equatorial Guinea are heading into the game on the back of eight matches without a defeat but they have been unable to get over 1.5 goals in any of the last four matches.

Equatorial Guinea have been able to enjoy majority of their recent success owing to a strong defensive display in recent matches. This is explained by the team picking up back-to-back clean sheets in two different competitions.
Liberia are without a goal in the last two games.
